HEADWORD: Nethinim
<hw>Neth"i*nim</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[Heb., pl.
of <ets>n⟦amac⟧th⟦imac⟧n</ets> given, granted, a slave of the temple,
fr. <ets>n⟦amac⟧than</ets> to give.]</ety> <fld>(jewish Antiq.)</fld>
<def>Servants of the priests and Levites in the menial services about
the tabernacle and temple.</def>⟦br⟧
